text: Jenna Rheault is an American ice hockey defender, currently playing for the Boston Pride in the NWHL. == Career == Across four seasons with the University of New Hampshire, Rheault scored 24 points in 142 games, being noted for her defensive abilities, blocking over 50 shots every season.https://www.mainstmag.com/single-post/2019/04/30/Featuring-Jenna- Rheaulthttps://unhwildcats.com/roster.aspx?rp_id=7233&path;=whockey Rheault was selected 25th overall by the Pride in the 2018 NWHL Draft.https://www.concordmonitor.com/UNHPlayerDraftedFB-CMSP-122118-22307723 She would become the first player from that draft class to sign in the NWHL when she joined the Pride in May 2019.https://thehockeywriters.com/boston- pride-signs-jenna-rheault/ She would put up 6 points in 24 games in her rookie season, as the Pride finished first in the league.https://www.unionleader.com/sports/deerings-jenna-rheault-hopes-rookie- season-will-end-with-nwhl- title/article_9ef00065-d29b-5c40-bf2e-61c727342154.htmlhttps://www.unionleader.com/sports/deering- s-jenna-rheault-settling-in-with-nwhl-s- boston/article_74bc4f97-f65a-5a94-9ad9-82e7b2e341a8.html === International === Rheault participated in the USA National Development Camp from 2009 to 2012, but has yet to make an appearance for the American national team. == Personal life == Her brother Jon currently plays for the Nottingham Panthers in the EIHL. == References == ==External links== * Biographical information and career statistics from Elite Prospects Category:Boston Pride players Category:1996 births Category:Living people Category:American women's ice hockey defensemen Category:Ice hockey people from New Hampshire
